  "texts": [
    "Tasks can be solved more effectively by matching their computational requirements with the appropriate encoding scale.",
    "Note that DeCorr is different from the DeCov loss function previously developed to reduce overfitting 53.",
    "DeCorr decorrelates pairs of inputs across all neurons in the specified layer, whereas DeCov decorrelates pairs of neurons across all inputs.",
    "As a regularizer that promotes generalization, DeCov improves digit classification and does not substantially improve set identification, which contrasts with the effect of DeCorr (Supplementary Fig. 8C, D).",
    "Complex tasks, including those performed by biological systems, may require information to be processed at different scales of correlation."
